{
  "analysis": "The terminal is still flooded by the earlier `findexact` brute-force process. Previous Ctrl-C and kill attempts were interleaved with ongoing output, so we need a minimal, reliable stabilization step before diagnostics or encoder fixes. Known evidence: `4f 02` decompresses to `01`, while our generated non-empty streams are invalid. Once stable, clean `decsim` diagnostics comparing `4f 02` versus `/app/t1.comp` are needed to identify the arithmetic encoder bug.",
  "plan": "Send one Ctrl-C to interrupt the foreground process, wait briefly, then run a single robust kill loop that kills all `findexact`/`brute3` PIDs and writes a marker. After that, poll the process list to confirm cleanup. No diagnostics will be run in this batch to avoid further interleaving.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in $(seq 1 10); do pids=$(pgrep -f 'findexact|brute3'); if [ -z \"$pids\" ]; then echo NONE; break; fi; kill -9 $pids 2>/dev/null; sleep 0.3; done; echo STABLE\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pgrep -af 'findexact|brute3' || echo CLEANED\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
